'''Aaron Payas''' (born 24 May 1985) is a Gibraltarian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Europa F.C.|Europa]]<ref>[https://twitter.com/FootballGib/status/1028613138978164736 Payas joins Europa] Football Gibraltar on [[Twitter]]. 12 August 2018. Retrieved 19 August 2018.</ref> and the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] national team, where he plays as a [[midfielder]].
==International career== [[File:Gibratlar v. Faroe Islands friendly football match 1 March 2014 (7).jpg|thumb|250px|Payas playing for Gibraltar against the Faroe Islands on his début.]] Payas was first called up to the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar senior team]] in February 2014 for [[exhibition match|friendlies]] against [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] and [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]] on 1 and 5 March 2014.<ref name="GFA reveals squads">{{cite web|title=GFA reveals squads for upcoming friendlies |url=http://www.gbc.gi/news/3190/gfa-reveals-squads-for-upcoming-friendlies |publisher=GBC |accessdate=4 March 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222015049/http://www.gbc.gi/news/3190/gfa-reveals-squads-for-upcoming-friendlies |archivedate=22 February 2014 }}</ref><ref name="Faroe Islands and Estonia">{{cite web|title=Squad for Faroe Islands and Estonia friendlies announced|url=http://footballgibraltar.wordpress.com/2014/02/11/squad-for-faroe-islands-and-estonia-friendlies-announced/|work=footballgibraltar.wordpress.com/|accessdate=4 March 2014}}</ref> He made his international début with Gibraltar on 1 March 2014 in a 4-1 home loss with the [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]].<ref name="gib debut">{{cite news|title=Gibraltar crash back down to earth with heavy Faroe Islands loss|url=http://nonfifafootball.blogspot.co.uk/2014/03/the-reality-of-uefa-international.html|accessdate=4 March 2014|date=1 March 2014}}</ref> His second appearance came a 2-0 home loss to [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]] on 5 March 2014.
