The '''ECHL Goaltender of the Year''' is an [[ice hockey]] award presented annually by the [[ECHL]] to the goaltender adjudged to be the best at his position. This award was first presented in [[1993–94 ECHL season|1994]] to [[Cory Cadden]] of the [[Knoxville Cherokees]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.echl.com/reebok-goaltender-of-the-year-winners-p144415 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-08-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150720203502/http://www.echl.com/reebok-goaltender-of-the-year-winners-p144415 |archivedate=2015-07-20 |df= }}</ref>
